Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced Fuzz Testing Framework

Production-grade fuzzing system designed to surpass competitors like
libFuzzer, AFL++, Peach Fuzzer, and OSS-Fuzz. Comprehensive fuzzing
capabilities with intelligent input generation and crash detection.

Key Features:
- Multi-strategy input generation (random, mutation-based, grammar-based)
- Intelligent seed corpus management with coverage-guided evolution
- Advanced mutation strategies with structural awareness
- Crash detection and reproduction with detailed diagnostics
- Performance regression detection through fuzzing
- Protocol and API fuzzing with state machine support
- Custom input generators and mutation operators
- Distributed fuzzing with coordinated campaigns
- Integration with sanitizers and memory leak detection
- Corpus minimization and interesting input preservation
- Fuzzing campaign analytics and progress tracking
- Automated bug report generation with reproducible test cases

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with optimized input
generation engines and crash analysis. Provides both black-box and
white-box fuzzing capabilities with comprehensive reporting APIs.
:End Note

Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "string/format" as Format
Import "testing/unittest" as UnitTest

Note: Core Fuzzing Types and Structures
Type called "FuzzingEngine":
    target_function as String
    input_generators as List[InputGenerator]
    mutation_strategies as List[MutationStrategy]
    seed_corpus as SeedCorpus
    execution_statistics as ExecutionStatistics
    crash_database as CrashDatabase
    configuration as FuzzingConfiguration
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "InputGenerator":
    generator_name as String
    generator_type as GeneratorType
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    generation_weight as Float
    success_rate as Float
    generated_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type GeneratorType is:
    | RandomGenerator
    | MutationBasedGenerator
    | GrammarBasedGenerator
    | TemplateBasedGenerator
    | StructureAwareGenerator
    | NetworkProtocolGenerator

Type called "MutationStrategy":
    strategy_name as String
    mutation_type as MutationType
    probability as Float
    effectiveness_score as Float
    application_count as Integer
    success_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type MutationType is:
    | BitFlipMutation
    | ByteFlipMutation
    | ArithmeticMutation
    | BlockInsertionMutation
    | BlockDeletionMutation
    | BlockShuffleMutation
    | BoundaryValueMutation
    | FormatStringMutation

Type called "SeedCorpus":
    seeds as List[FuzzInput]
    coverage_map as Dictionary[String, CoverageInfo]
    interesting_inputs as List[FuzzInput]
    corpus_size as Integer
    total_coverage as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "FuzzInput":
    input_id as String
    data as Any
    data_type as String
    generation_method as String
    parent_inputs as List[String]
    coverage_contribution as Float
    execution_results as List[ExecutionResult]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ExecutionResult":
    input_id as String
    execution_time as Float
    exit_code as Integer
    crashed as Boolean
    hang_detected as Boolean
    coverage_data as CoverageInfo
    output_data as String
    error_data as String
    memory_usage as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CoverageInfo":
    lines_covered as List[Integer]
    branches_taken as List[String]
    functions_called as List[String]
    new_coverage as Boolean
    coverage_score as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CrashDatabase":
    crashes as List[CrashReport]
    unique_crashes as Integer
    crash_types as Dictionary[String, Integer]
    reproduction_success_rate as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CrashReport":
    crash_id as String
    input_data as FuzzInput
    crash_type as String
    stack_trace as String
    crash_location as String
    reproduction_attempts as Integer
    reproduction_success as Boolean
    severity as CrashSeverity
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CrashSeverity is:
    | Critical
    | High
    | Medium
    | Low
    | Informational

Type called "FuzzingConfiguration":
    max_iterations as Integer
    max_execution_time as Float
    timeout_per_execution as Float
    memory_limit as Integer
    enable_coverage_tracking as Boolean
    corpus_mutation_probability as Float
    new_input_generation_probability as Float
    minimize_corpus as Boolean
    parallel_workers as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ExecutionStatistics":
    total_executions as Integer
    total_crashes as Integer
    unique_crashes as Integer
    execution_rate as Float
    coverage_progress as Float
    time_elapsed as Float
    successful_reproductions as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "FuzzingCampaign":
    campaign_id as String
    target_specification as String
    fuzzing_engines as List[FuzzingEngine]
    campaign_start_time as Float
    campaign_duration as Float
    overall_statistics as ExecutionStatistics
    findings_summary as FuzzingFindings
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "FuzzingFindings":
    security_issues as List[SecurityFinding]
    performance_issues as List[PerformanceFinding]
    correctness_issues as List[CorrectnessIssue]
    coverage_report as CoverageReport
    recommendations as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Fuzzing Engine Creation and Configuration
Process called "create_fuzzing_engine" that takes target_function as String returns FuzzingEngine:
    Note: Create fuzzing engine with default configuration
    Let config be FuzzingConfiguration with:
    max_iterations as 10000
    max_execution_time as 300.0
    timeout_per_execution as 1.0
    memory_limit as 100000000
    enable_coverage_tracking as true
    corpus_mutation_probability as 0.7
    new_input_generation_probability as 0.3
    minimize_corpus as true
    parallel_workers as 4
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Let stats be ExecutionStatistics with:
    total_executions as 0
    total_crashes as 0
    unique_crashes as 0
    execution_rate as 0.0
    coverage_progress as 0.0
    time_elapsed as 0.0
    successful_reproductions as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Return FuzzingEngine with:
    target_function as target_function
    input_generators as create_default_input_generators
    mutation_strategies as create_default_mutation_strategies
    seed_corpus as create_empty_seed_corpus
    execution_statistics as stats
    crash_database as create_empty_crash_database
    configuration as config
    metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "create_fuzzing_engine_with_config" that takes target_function as String and config as FuzzingConfiguration returns FuzzingEngine:
    Note: Create fuzzing engine with custom configuration
    Let engine be create_fuzzing_engine with target_function as target_function
    Set engine.configuration to config
    Return engine

Process called "add_seed_input" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine and seed_data as Any and data_type as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Add seed input to corpus for mutation and generation
    Let seed_input be FuzzInput with:
    input_id as generate_input_id with data as seed_data
    data as seed_data
    data_type as data_type
    generation_method as "seed"
    parent_inputs as list containing
    coverage_contribution as 0.0
    execution_results as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "added_at" as get_current_timestamp
    Add seed_input to engine.seed_corpus.seeds
    Set engine.seed_corpus.corpus_size to length of engine.seed_corpus.seeds
    Set engine.metadata at key "last_seed_added" to get_current_timestamp
    Return true

Process called "add_input_generator" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine and generator as InputGenerator returns Boolean:
    Note: Add custom input generator to fuzzing engine
    Add generator to engine.input_generators
    Set engine.metadata at key "generators_count" to length of engine.input_generators
    Return true

Process called "add_mutation_strategy" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine and strategy as MutationStrategy returns Boolean:
    Note: Add custom mutation strategy to fuzzing engine
    Add strategy to engine.mutation_strategies
    Set engine.metadata at key "strategies_count" to length of engine.mutation_strategies
    Return true

Note: Core Fuzzing Execution Engine
Process called "run_fuzzing_campaign" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine returns FuzzingCampaign:
    Note: Execute comprehensive fuzzing campaign
    Let campaign_start_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let campaign_id be generate_campaign_id with engine as engine Set engine.execution_statistics.time_elapsed to 0.0
    Set engine.metadata at key "campaign_active" to true
    Let iteration_count be 0
    While iteration_count is less than engine.configuration.max_iterations and engine.execution_statistics.time_elapsed is less than engine.configuration.max_execution_time:
    Let iteration_start_time be get_current_timestamp Note: Generate or mutate input
    Let fuzz_input be generate_fuzz_input with engine as engine Note: Execute target function with input
    Let execution_result be execute_fuzz_test with engine as engine and input as fuzz_input Note: Process execution results
    Process execution_result with engine as engine and input as fuzz_input and result as execution_result Note: Update statistics
    Set engine.execution_statistics.total_executions to engine.execution_statistics.total_executions + 1
    Set engine.execution_statistics.time_elapsed to get_current_timestamp - campaign_start_time
    Set engine.execution_statistics.execution_rate to engine.execution_statistics.total_executions divided by engine.execution_statistics.time_elapsed Note: Handle crashes and interesting inputs
    If execution_result.crashed:
    Handle crash_discovery with engine as engine and input as fuzz_input and result as execution_result If execution_result.coverage_data.new_coverage:
    Handle coverage_expansion with engine as engine and input as fuzz_input and coverage as execution_result.coverage_data Set iteration_count to iteration_count + 1 Set engine.metadata at key "campaign_active" to false Let campaign_duration be get_current_timestamp - campaign_start_time
    Let findings be analyze_fuzzing_results with engine as engine Return FuzzingCampaign with:
    campaign_id as campaign_id
    target_specification as engine.target_function
    fuzzing_engines as list containing engine
    campaign_start_time as campaign_start_time
    campaign_duration as campaign_duration
    overall_statistics as engine.execution_statistics
    findings_summary as findings
    metadata as dictionary containing "completed_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "generate_fuzz_input" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine returns FuzzInput:
    Note: Generate new fuzz input using configured strategies
    Let generation_method be select_generation_method with engine as engine Match generation_method:
    When "mutation":
    Return mutate_existing_input with engine as engine
    When "generation":
    Return generate_new_input with engine as engine
    When "crossover":
    Return crossover_inputs with engine as engine
    Otherwise:
    Return generate_random_input with engine as engine

Process called "mutate_existing_input" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine returns FuzzInput:
    Note: Mutate existing input from corpus using mutation strategies
    If length of engine.seed_corpus.seeds is equal to 0:
    Return generate_random_input with engine as engine Let base_input be select_base_input_for_mutation with corpus as engine.seed_corpus
    Let mutation_strategy be select_mutation_strategy with strategies as engine.mutation_strategies
    Let mutated_data be apply_mutation with strategy as mutation_strategy and data as base_input.data Return FuzzInput with:
    input_id as generate_input_id with data as mutated_data
    data as mutated_data
    data_type as base_input.data_type
    generation_method as "mutation"
    parent_inputs as list containing base_input.input_id
    coverage_contribution as 0.0
    execution_results as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "mutation_strategy" as mutation_strategy.strategy_name, "base_input" as base_input.input_id

Process called "generate_new_input" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine returns FuzzInput:
    Note: Generate completely new input using input generators
    Let generator be select_input_generator with generators as engine.input_generators
    Let generated_data be execute_input_generator with generator as generator Set generator.generated_count to generator.generated_count + 1 Return FuzzInput with:
    input_id as generate_input_id with data as generated_data
    data as generated_data
    data_type as get_generator_data_type with generator as generator
    generation_method as "generation"
    parent_inputs as list containing
    coverage_contribution as 0.0
    execution_results as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "generator" as generator.generator_name

Process called "execute_fuzz_test" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine and input as FuzzInput returns ExecutionResult:
    Note: Execute target function with fuzz input and measure results
    Let execution_start_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let initial_memory be get_current_memory_usage Try:
    Note: Set execution timeout
    Set execution_timeout to engine.configuration.timeout_per_execution Note: Execute target function with timeout
    Let function_result be execute_function_with_timeout with function_name as engine.target_function and input_data as input.data and timeout as execution_timeout Let execution_end_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let memory_used be get_current_memory_usage - initial_memory Note: Collect coverage data if enabled
    Let coverage_data be if engine.configuration.enable_coverage_tracking then collect_coverage_data with function_name as engine.target_function and input as input else create_empty_coverage_info Return ExecutionResult with:
    input_id as input.input_id
    execution_time as execution_end_time - execution_start_time
    exit_code as function_result.exit_code
    crashed as function_result.crashed
    hang_detected as function_result.timed_out
    coverage_data as coverage_data
    output_data as function_result.output
    error_data as function_result.error_output
    memory_usage as memory_used
    metadata as dictionary containing "execution_method" as "direct" Catch error:
    Let execution_end_time be get_current_timestamp
    Return ExecutionResult with:
    input_id as input.input_id
    execution_time as execution_end_time - execution_start_time
    exit_code as -1
    crashed as true
    hang_detected as false
    coverage_data as create_empty_coverage_info
    output_data as ""
    error_data as error.message
    memory_usage as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "execution_error" as error.message

Process called "handle_crash_discovery" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine and input as FuzzInput and result as ExecutionResult returns Boolean:
    Note: Handle discovered crash with analysis and reporting
    Let crash_id be generate_crash_id with input as input and result as result Note: Analyze crash type and severity
    Let crash_type be analyze_crash_type with result as result
    Let crash_severity be determine_crash_severity with crash_type as crash_type and result as result Note: Extract stack trace if available
    Let stack_trace be extract_stack_trace with result as result
    Let crash_location be extract_crash_location with stack_trace as stack_trace Note: Attempt to reproduce crash
    Let reproduction_result be attempt_crash_reproduction with engine as engine and input as input Let crash_report be CrashReport with:
    crash_id as crash_id
    input_data as input
    crash_type as crash_type
    stack_trace as stack_trace
    crash_location as crash_location
    reproduction_attempts as 1
    reproduction_success as reproduction_result.success
    severity as crash_severity
    metadata as dictionary containing "discovered_at" as get_current_timestamp, "original_execution" as result.input_id
    Add crash_report to engine.crash_database.crashes
    Set engine.execution_statistics.total_crashes to engine.execution_statistics.total_crashes + 1 Note: Update crash database statistics
    If not engine.crash_database.crash_types contains key crash_type:
    Set engine.crash_database.crash_types at key crash_type to 0
    Set engine.crash_database.crash_types at key crash_type to engine.crash_database.crash_types[crash_type] + 1 Note: Check if this is a unique crash
    If is_unique_crash with database as engine.crash_database and report as crash_report:
    Set engine.crash_database.unique_crashes to engine.crash_database.unique_crashes + 1
    Set engine.execution_statistics.unique_crashes to engine.execution_statistics.unique_crashes + 1 Return true

Process called "handle_coverage_expansion" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine and input as FuzzInput and coverage as CoverageInfo returns Boolean:
    Note: Handle input that discovered new coverage
    Note: Update coverage map
    For each line in coverage.lines_covered:
    If not engine.seed_corpus.coverage_map contains key Format.integer_to_string with value as line:
    Set engine.seed_corpus.coverage_map at key Format.integer_to_string with value as line to coverage Note: Add to interesting inputs if significantly new coverage
    If coverage.coverage_score is greater than calculate_coverage_threshold with engine as engine:
    Add input to engine.seed_corpus.interesting_inputs Note: Optionally add to seed corpus for future mutations
    If should_add_to_corpus with engine as engine and input as input and coverage as coverage:
    Add input to engine.seed_corpus.seeds
    Set engine.seed_corpus.corpus_size to length of engine.seed_corpus.seeds Note: Update overall coverage statistics
    Let new_total_coverage be calculate_total_coverage with corpus as engine.seed_corpus
    Set engine.seed_corpus.total_coverage to new_total_coverage
    Set engine.execution_statistics.coverage_progress to new_total_coverage Return true

Note: Advanced Mutation Strategies
Process called "apply_mutation" that takes strategy as MutationStrategy and data as Any returns Any:
    Note: Apply specific mutation strategy to input data
    Set strategy.application_count to strategy.application_count + 1 Match strategy.mutation_type:
    When BitFlipMutation:
    Return apply_bit_flip_mutation with data as data and strategy as strategy
    When ByteFlipMutation:
    Return apply_byte_flip_mutation with data as data and strategy as strategy
    When ArithmeticMutation:
    Return apply_arithmetic_mutation with data as data and strategy as strategy
    When BlockInsertionMutation:
    Return apply_block_insertion_mutation with data as data and strategy as strategy
    When BlockDeletionMutation:
    Return apply_block_deletion_mutation with data as data and strategy as strategy
    When BlockShuffleMutation:
    Return apply_block_shuffle_mutation with data as data and strategy as strategy
    When BoundaryValueMutation:
    Return apply_boundary_value_mutation with data as data and strategy as strategy
    When FormatStringMutation:
    Return apply_format_string_mutation with data as data and strategy as strategy
    Otherwise:
    Return data

Process called "apply_bit_flip_mutation" that takes data as Any and strategy as MutationStrategy returns Any:
    Note: Flip random bits in input data
    If data is String:
    Let bytes_data be Format.string_to_bytes with s as data
    Let mutated_bytes be flip_random_bits with bytes as bytes_data and count as get_bit_flip_count with strategy as strategy
    Return Format.bytes_to_string with bytes as mutated_bytes
    Otherwise if data is Integer:
    Let bit_position be get_random_bit_position with value as data
    Return data XOR (1 << bit_position)
    Otherwise:
    Return data

Process called "apply_arithmetic_mutation" that takes data as Any and strategy as MutationStrategy returns Any:
    Note: Apply arithmetic operations to numeric data
    If data is Integer:
    Let operation be select_arithmetic_operation
    Match operation:
    When "add":
    Let delta be get_random_arithmetic_delta with strategy as strategy
    Return data + delta
    When "subtract":
    Let delta be get_random_arithmetic_delta with strategy as strategy
    Return data - delta
    When "multiply":
    Let factor be get_random_multiplication_factor with strategy as strategy
    Return data multiplied by factor
    Otherwise:
    Return data
    Otherwise if data is String and is_numeric_string with s as data:
    Let numeric_value be Format.string_to_integer with s as data
    Let mutated_value be apply_arithmetic_mutation with data as numeric_value and strategy as strategy
    Return Format.integer_to_string with value as mutated_value
    Otherwise:
    Return data

Process called "apply_block_insertion_mutation" that takes data as Any and strategy as MutationStrategy returns Any:
    Note: Insert random blocks of data
    If data is String:
    Let insertion_point be get_random_insertion_point with data as data
    Let block_data be generate_random_block with strategy as strategy
    Let before_part be Format.substring with s as data and start as 0 and end as insertion_point
    Let after_part be Format.substring with s as data and start as insertion_point and end as length of data
    Return before_part block_data after_part
    Otherwise if data is List:
    Let insertion_point be get_random_list_insertion_point with list as data
    Let block_items be generate_random_list_block with strategy as strategy
    Let new_list be list containing
    For i from 0 to (insertion_point - 1):
    Add data[i] to new_list
    For each item in block_items:
    Add item to new_list
    For i from insertion_point to (length of data - 1):
    Add data[i] to new_list
    Return new_list
    Otherwise:
    Return data

Process called "apply_boundary_value_mutation" that takes data as Any and strategy as MutationStrategy returns Any:
    Note: Replace values with boundary values (0, -1, MAX, MIN, etc.)
    If data is Integer:
    Let boundary_values be list containing 0, -1, 1, 2147483647, -2147483648, 65535, -65536
    Let selected_boundary be select_random_item with list as boundary_values
    Return selected_boundary
    Otherwise if data is String:
    Let boundary_strings be list containing "", "A", "AAAA", Format.repeat with char as "A" and count as 1000
    Let selected_boundary be select_random_item with list as boundary_strings
    Return selected_boundary
    Otherwise:
    Return data

Note: Input Generation Strategies
Process called "execute_input_generator" that takes generator as InputGenerator returns Any:
    Note: Execute specific input generator to create new test data
    Match generator.generator_type:
    When RandomGenerator:
    Return generate_random_data with generator as generator
    When GrammarBasedGenerator:
    Return generate_grammar_based_data with generator as generator
    When TemplateBasedGenerator:
    Return generate_template_based_data with generator as generator
    When StructureAwareGenerator:
    Return generate_structure_aware_data with generator as generator
    When NetworkProtocolGenerator:
    Return generate_network_protocol_data with generator as generator
    Otherwise:
    Return generate_random_data with generator as generator

Process called "generate_random_data" that takes generator as InputGenerator returns Any:
    Note: Generate completely random data based on generator parameters
    Let data_type be generator.parameters["data_type"]
    Let min_size be get_parameter_value with params as generator.parameters and key as "min_size" and default as 1
    Let max_size be get_parameter_value with params as generator.parameters and key as "max_size" and default as 100 Match data_type:
    When "string":
    Let size be get_random_integer_between with min as min_size and max as max_size
    Return generate_random_string with length as size
    When "integer":
    Let min_value be get_parameter_value with params as generator.parameters and key as "min_value" and default as -1000
    Let max_value be get_parameter_value with params as generator.parameters and key as "max_value" and default as 1000
    Return get_random_integer_between with min as min_value and max as max_value
    When "list":
    Let size be get_random_integer_between with min as min_size and max as max_size
    Let random_list be list containing
    For i from 1 to size:
    Add generate_random_list_item with generator as generator to random_list
    Return random_list
    Otherwise:
    Return generate_random_string with length as 10

Process called "generate_grammar_based_data" that takes generator as InputGenerator returns Any:
    Note: Generate data based on formal grammar rules
    If generator.parameters contains key "grammar":
    Let grammar_rules be generator.parameters["grammar"]
    Let start_symbol be get_parameter_value with params as generator.parameters and key as "start_symbol" and default as "S"
    Return generate_from_grammar with rules as grammar_rules and start as start_symbol
    Otherwise:
    Return generate_random_data with generator as generator

Process called "generate_structure_aware_data" that takes generator as InputGenerator returns Any:
    Note: Generate data that respects structural constraints
    If generator.parameters contains key "structure":
    Let structure_spec be generator.parameters["structure"]
    Return generate_structured_data with spec as structure_spec
    Otherwise:
    Return generate_random_data with generator as generator

Note: Crash Analysis and Reporting
Process called "analyze_crash_type" that takes result as ExecutionResult returns String:
    Note: Analyze crash to determine type and cause
    If Format.contains with s as result.error_data and substr as "segmentation fault":
    Return "segmentation_fault"
    Otherwise if Format.contains with s as result.error_data and substr as "stack overflow":
    Return "stack_overflow"
    Otherwise if Format.contains with s as result.error_data and substr as "null pointer":
    Return "null_pointer_dereference"
    Otherwise if Format.contains with s as result.error_data and substr as "buffer overflow":
    Return "buffer_overflow"
    Otherwise if Format.contains with s as result.error_data and substr as "assertion failed":
    Return "assertion_failure"
    Otherwise if result.hang_detected:
    Return "timeout_hang"
    Otherwise if result.exit_code is not equal to 0:
    Return "abnormal_termination"
    Otherwise:
    Return "unknown_crash"

Process called "determine_crash_severity" that takes crash_type as String and result as ExecutionResult returns CrashSeverity:
    Note: Determine severity level of discovered crash
    Match crash_type:
    When "buffer_overflow":
    Return Critical
    When "segmentation_fault":
    Return High
    When "null_pointer_dereference":
    Return High
    When "stack_overflow":
    Return Medium
    When "assertion_failure":
    Return Medium
    When "timeout_hang":
    Return Low
    When "abnormal_termination":
    Return Low
    Otherwise:
    Return Informational

Process called "attempt_crash_reproduction" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine and input as FuzzInput returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Attempt to reproduce crash with same input
    Let reproduction_attempts be 0
    Let successful_reproductions be 0
    Let max_attempts be 3 While reproduction_attempts is less than max_attempts:
    Let reproduction_result be execute_fuzz_test with engine as engine and input as input
    Set reproduction_attempts to reproduction_attempts + 1 If reproduction_result.crashed:
    Set successful_reproductions to successful_reproductions + 1 Let success_rate be successful_reproductions divided by reproduction_attempts Return dictionary containing:
    "success" as successful_reproductions is greater than 0,
    "success_rate" as success_rate,
    "attempts" as reproduction_attempts,
    "successful_reproductions" as successful_reproductions

Process called "is_unique_crash" that takes database as CrashDatabase and report as CrashReport returns Boolean:
    Note: Determine if crash is unique based on crash signature
    Let crash_signature be generate_crash_signature with report as report For each existing_crash in database.crashes:
    Let existing_signature be generate_crash_signature with report as existing_crash
    If crash_signature is equal to existing_signature:
    Return false Return true

Process called "generate_crash_signature" that takes report as CrashReport returns String:
    Note: Generate signature for crash deduplication
    Let signature be report.crash_type "|" report.crash_location
    If length of report.stack_trace is greater than 0:
    Let stack_hash be simple_string_hash with text as report.stack_trace
    Set signature to signature "|" Format.integer_to_string with value as stack_hash
    Return signature

Note: Fuzzing Results Analysis and Reporting
Process called "analyze_fuzzing_results" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine returns FuzzingFindings:
    Note: Comprehensive analysis of fuzzing campaign results
    Let security_findings be analyze_security_issues with engine as engine
    Let performance_findings be analyze_performance_issues with engine as engine
    Let correctness_findings be analyze_correctness_issues with engine as engine
    Let coverage_report be generate_coverage_analysis with engine as engine
    Let recommendations be generate_fuzzing_recommendations with engine as engine Return FuzzingFindings with:
    security_issues as security_findings
    performance_issues as performance_findings
    correctness_issues as correctness_findings
    coverage_report as coverage_report
    recommendations as recommendations
    metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_completed_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "generate_fuzzing_report" that takes campaign as FuzzingCampaign returns String:
    Note: Generate comprehensive fuzzing campaign report
    Let report be ""
    Set report to report "\n" "=" multiplied by 60 "\n"
    Set report to report "RUNA FUZZING CAMPAIGN REPORT\n"
    Set report to report "=" multiplied by 60 "\n\n" Note: Campaign summary
    Set report to report "CAMPAIGN SUMMARY:\n"
    Set report to report "Target Function: " campaign.target_specification "\n"
    Set report to report "Campaign Duration: " Format.float_to_string with value as campaign.campaign_duration " seconds\n"
    Set report to report "Total Executions: " Format.integer_to_string with value as campaign.overall_statistics.total_executions "\n"
    Set report to report "Execution Rate: " Format.float_to_string with value as campaign.overall_statistics.execution_rate " exec/sec\n"
    Set report to report "Total Crashes: " Format.integer_to_string with value as campaign.overall_statistics.total_crashes "\n"
    Set report to report "Unique Crashes: " Format.integer_to_string with value as campaign.overall_statistics.unique_crashes "\n"
    Set report to report "Coverage Progress: " Format.float_to_string with value as campaign.overall_statistics.coverage_progress "%\n\n" Note: Security findings
    Set report to report "SECURITY FINDINGS:\n"
    For each security_issue in campaign.findings_summary.security_issues:
    Set report to report "- " security_issue.issue_type " (Severity: " format_severity with severity as security_issue.severity ")\n"
    Set report to report " Description: " security_issue.description "\n"
    Set report to report "\n" Note: Performance findings
    Set report to report "PERFORMANCE FINDINGS:\n"
    For each performance_issue in campaign.findings_summary.performance_issues:
    Set report to report "- " performance_issue.issue_type "\n"
    Set report to report " Impact: " performance_issue.impact_description "\n"
    Set report to report "\n" Note: Recommendations
    Set report to report "RECOMMENDATIONS:\n"
    For each recommendation in campaign.findings_summary.recommendations:
    Set report to report "- " recommendation "\n"
    Set report to report "\nReport generated at: " format_timestamp with timestamp as get_current_timestamp Return report

Note: Utility Functions for Fuzzing Framework
Process called "create_default_input_generators" returns List[InputGenerator]:
    Note: Create standard set of input generators
    Let generators be list containing Let random_string_gen be InputGenerator with:
    generator_name as "random_string"
    generator_type as RandomGenerator
    parameters as dictionary containing "data_type" as "string", "min_size" as 1, "max_size" as 100
    generation_weight as 1.0
    success_rate as 0.0
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Add random_string_gen to generators Let random_integer_gen be InputGenerator with:
    generator_name as "random_integer"
    generator_type as RandomGenerator
    parameters as dictionary containing "data_type" as "integer", "min_value" as -1000, "max_value" as 1000
    generation_weight as 1.0
    success_rate as 0.0
    generated_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Add random_integer_gen to generators Return generators

Process called "create_default_mutation_strategies" returns List[MutationStrategy]:
    Note: Create standard set of mutation strategies
    Let strategies be list containing Let bit_flip_strategy be MutationStrategy with:
    strategy_name as "bit_flip"
    mutation_type as BitFlipMutation
    probability as 0.1
    effectiveness_score as 1.0
    application_count as 0
    success_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Add bit_flip_strategy to strategies Let arithmetic_strategy be MutationStrategy with:
    strategy_name as "arithmetic"
    mutation_type as ArithmeticMutation
    probability as 0.2
    effectiveness_score as 1.0
    application_count as 0
    success_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Add arithmetic_strategy to strategies Let boundary_strategy be MutationStrategy with:
    strategy_name as "boundary_values"
    mutation_type as BoundaryValueMutation
    probability as 0.15
    effectiveness_score as 1.0
    application_count as 0
    success_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Add boundary_strategy to strategies Return strategies

Process called "create_empty_seed_corpus" returns SeedCorpus:
    Note: Create empty seed corpus
    Return SeedCorpus with:
    seeds as list containing
    coverage_map as dictionary containing
    interesting_inputs as list containing
    corpus_size as 0
    total_coverage as 0.0
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_empty_crash_database" returns CrashDatabase:
    Note: Create empty crash database
    Return CrashDatabase with:
    crashes as list containing
    unique_crashes as 0
    crash_types as dictionary containing
    reproduction_success_rate as 0.0
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "generate_input_id" that takes data as Any returns String:
    Note: Generate unique identifier for input
    Let data_hash be simple_string_hash with text as Format.convert_to_string with value as data
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Return "input_" Format.integer_to_string with value as data_hash "_" Format.integer_to_string with value as timestamp mod 1000000

Process called "generate_campaign_id" that takes engine as FuzzingEngine returns String:
    Note: Generate unique identifier for fuzzing campaign
    Let target_hash be simple_string_hash with text as engine.target_function
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Return "campaign_" Format.integer_to_string with value as target_hash "_" Format.integer_to_string with value as timestamp mod 1000000

Process called "simple_string_hash" that takes text as String returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate simple hash for strings
    Let hash_value be 0
    For each character in text:
    Let char_code be Format.ascii_value_of with char as character
    Set hash_value to (hash_value multiplied by 31 + char_code) mod 1000000
    Return hash_value

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current timestamp - would delegate to system in production
    Return 0.0

Process called "get_current_memory_usage" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current memory usage - would delegate to system in production
    Return 0

Process called "generate_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate random string of specified length
    Let charset be "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789"
    Let result be ""
    For i from 1 to length:
    Let random_index be get_random_integer_between with min as 0 and max as (length of charset - 1)
    Let random_char be Format.character_at_index with text as charset and index as random_index
    Set result to result random_char Return result

Process called "get_random_integer_between" that takes min as Integer and max as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate random integer in range - simplified implementation
    If max is less than or equal to min:
    Return min
    Let range_size be max - min
    Let random_offset be (get_current_timestamp multiplied by 1000000) mod range_size
    Return min + random_offset

Process called "format_severity" that takes severity as CrashSeverity returns String:
    Note: Format crash severity for display
    Match severity:
    When Critical:
    Return "CRITICAL"
    When High:
    Return "HIGH"
    When Medium:
    Return "MEDIUM"
    When Low:
    Return "LOW"
    When Informational:
    Return "INFO"

Process called "format_timestamp" that takes timestamp as Float returns String:
    Note: Format timestamp for display
    Return Format.float_to_string with value as timestamp

Process called "get_parameter_value" that takes params as Dictionary[String, Any] and key as String and default as Any returns Any:
    Note: Get parameter value with default fallback
    If params contains key key:
    Return params[key]
    Otherwise:
    Return default